{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1f44f4f0-7795-499f-8ba9-e6d03213662b","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the file order in the `.fsproj`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_T0CAHMoFoBKH5rIY0naWyJ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-32cdd4a8dea74da9bcd4f36b302ef80b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-32cdd4a8dea74da9bcd4f36b302ef80b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"ff385c55-6d61-4aa3-9b13-4ffce3d25d20","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters because files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs - references `BrokenOrder.Domain` (but Domain.fs comes after it!)\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs - references both `BrokenOrder.Domain` and `BrokenOrder.Services`\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs (defines types used by Services)\n2. Services.fs (defines functions used by Program)\n3. Program.fs (the entry point)\n\n\nNow I'll reorder the file entries in the project file to fix this dependency chain.","outputTokens":452,"requestId":"5C04:158C5C:1DD0657:21982B5:6A07C8BA"},"id":"13ab7613-d52b-4cce-a0f3-ee6a95412726","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:30:42.811Z","parentId":"13726a36-aec0-4028-837e-a4baf4fb5f3f"}
